<item>
            <title>[SPARK-2182] Scalastyle rule blocking unicode operators</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-2182</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Some IDEs don&apos;t support Scala&apos;s &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scala-lang.org/old/node/4723&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;unicode operators&lt;/a&gt; so we should consider adding a scalastyle rule to block them for wider compatibility among contributors.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See this PR for a place we reverted a unicode operator: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/1119&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/1119&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
